Description: GSTB_BPT4 - Experimental evidence at protein level: Swiss-Prot protein existence level 1. Catalyzes the transfer of glucose from uridine diphosphoglucose to 5-hydroxymethyl cytosine of T4 DNA to yield glucosyl 5-hydroxymethyl cytosine (glc-HMC) (PubMed:22229759). This DNA process seems to occur immediately after DNA synthesis since the DNA alpha-glucosyltransferase interacts with the clamp protein gp45 (PubMed:22229759). The glc-HMC modification protects the phage genome against its own nucleases and the host restriction endonuclease system (PubMed:22229759). The glc-HMC modification also protects against the host CRISPR-Cas9 defense system (PubMed:26081634). From Enterobacteria phage T4 (Bacteriophage T4).
β-lactamase; bla; confers resistance to ampicillin, carbenicillin, and related antibiotics
transcription terminator for bacteriophage T7 RNA polymerase
bidirectional E. coli tonB-P14 transcription terminator
LacZα fragment of β-galactosidase; lacZ fragment
